    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "CCing @jiangtaoli2016 and @justinburke \r\n\r\nIf we are going to rename this code, we should think about using `HTTPS` as opposed to `TLS` since these credentials carry `HTTPS` semantics with domain name validation. This is in contrast with other usages for TLS such as www.spiffe.io which have different trust semantics and will probably have their own type of credentials."
