    "updated_at": "2017-12-14T01:34:17Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> `TlsWithServerHostNameValidation` would be a bit sad. Another solution\r\n> would be to keep TLS and add options for a given trust model where Server\r\n> Host Name validation would be the default.\r\n\r\n+1 to both these comments. The verbose name, while descriptive, is probably too verbose for the common case. I like the idea of adding an option to specify an alternative validation model.\r\n\r\n"
